        <h2 id="what-is">What is Originality.ai?</h2>
        <p>Originality.ai was founded in 2022 by Jonathan Gillham (an SEO veteran) specifically for the post-ChatGPT content era. The pitch: a single dashboard that tells you whether a piece of content is AI-generated, plagiarized, factually wrong, or simply unreadable — for clients, agencies, and publishers that take editorial standards seriously.</p>

        <p>The core product does five things:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>AI detector</strong> — scores text 0–100 for likelihood of AI generation across GPT, Claude, Gemini, Llama</li>
          <li><strong>Plagiarism check</strong> — open-web indexed comparison</li>
          <li><strong>Fact-checker</strong> — flags claims that don't match retrieval-grounded sources</li>
          <li><strong>Readability scoring</strong> — Flesch, grade level, sentence-length analysis</li>
          <li><strong>Site-wide AI scan</strong> — crawl your domain to flag pages likely to be AI-written</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="features">Originality.ai features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>

        <h3>1. AI detector</h3>
        <p>Paste text or upload a doc. Score 0–100 (0 = AI, 100 = human) with paragraph-level highlighting. Independently tested against datasets of GPT-4, Claude, Gemini and Llama output, Originality.ai consistently outperforms GPTZero on raw generation. Heavily edited or hybrid text is harder for everyone.</p>

        <h3>2. Plagiarism check</h3>
        <p>Bundled with AI detection. Web-indexed comparison flags matched passages with source URLs. Each scan deducts from your credit pool (Pro: 2,000 credits/month).</p>

        <h3>3. Fact-checker</h3>
        <p>Newer feature. Sends each factual claim to a retrieval step and returns "supported / unsupported / partial". Useful for catching invented stats from LLM-drafted content. Not infallible.</p>

        <h3>4. Site-wide scan</h3>
        <p>Crawl up to 1,000 URLs per scan to flag pages with high AI-likelihood scores. Useful for publishers auditing inherited content or after acquiring a site.</p>

        <h3>5. Team management + shareable reports</h3>
        <p>Tag scans for organization. Shareable reports via links or PDF export. Additional seats: $9.95/month (monthly) or $8.62/month (yearly) on Pro.</p>

        <h2 id="pricing">Originality.ai pricing — what it really costs in 2026</h2>

        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Plan</th><th>Monthly</th><th>Annual / mo</th><th>Credits</th><th>API</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="row-highlight"><td><strong>Pro</strong></td><td>$14.95</td><td>$12.95</td><td>2,000 / mo</td><td class="cell-no">No</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Enterprise</strong></td><td>$179</td><td>$136.58</td><td>30,000 / mo</td><td class="cell-yes">Yes</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Pay As You Go</strong></td><td>$30 one-time</td><td>—</td><td>3,000 (2-year expiry)</td><td class="cell-no">No</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p>Annual discount: Pro saves $24/year, Enterprise saves $509/year. Additional seats: Pro $9.95/mo (monthly) or $8.62/mo (yearly); Enterprise $24.95/mo (monthly) or $19.04/mo (yearly). 1 credit ≈ 100 words for AI detection or plagiarism.</p>

        <h3>The real monthly cost most reviews skip</h3>

